specialize

public final <U extends T> ListVocabulary<U> specialize(OWLClass listType,
                                                        java.lang.Class<U> itemAbstr)
Create a more special list vocabulary based on this vocabulary. The general contract is that listType is a sub class of list() and itemAbstraction is a sub class or sub interface of itemAbstraction().

Parameters:
listType - The OWL class which should be a sub class of the class returned by list().
itemAbstr - The more special Java class or interface used by the specialized list vocabulary.
Returns:
The more special list vocabulary.
